{"cursor":"3261","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox musical artist \n| name = Appliance image = caption = background = group_or_band origin = genre =\n| Post-rock years_active = 1995–2003 label = Mute website =\n| [http://www.myspace.com/applianceuk Myspace site] current_members = James\n| Brooks Michael Parker David Ireland past_members =\n}} 'Appliance' were a British experimental post-rock three piece, made up of\nJames Brooks (guitar), David Ireland (percussion) and Michael Parker (bass). [http://www.mute.com/artists/publicArtistLoad.do?id=1276&forward=longBio\n] Original bass player Stuart Christie left in 1995 to form Harmony 400.\n\nThey released three 10\" vinyl EPs on various independent record labels,\nincluding their own self-financed Surveillance Records, before signing with\nDaniel Miller's Mute Records in 1998.\n\nOn the Mute label they released Manual (1999), Six Modular Pieces (2000),\nImperial Metric(2001) and Are You Earthed? (2003). Their music was inspired by\nKrautrock, a 1970's Germanic experimental movement involving minimalist song\nstructures, mantra-like rhythms and drones. Championed by John Peel, the band\nrecorded four Peel Sessions during their career, Radio 1 Peel\nSessions and one in 2003 for Jeff Cooper's radio2XS. They toured live in\nEurope and the UK with, amongst others; Add N to X, Goldfrapp, Snow Patrol,\nHefner and Wire. The band have not performed or recorded since the Montreux\nJazz Festival in 2003.\n\nIn October 2010, the band released Appliance, Reconditioned, a retrospective 3-\nCD boxed set of early recordings, unreleased material and Peel sessions on the\n[http://www.rroopp.com/index.xml RROOPP] label.\n\nIn 2011, guitarist James Brooks as Land Observations, released the EP \"Roman\nRoads\" on [http://www.enrapturedrecords.com Enraptured Records]. In 2012, he\nreleased the album Roman Roads IVâXI on Mute.\n","linknr":122,"url":"Appliance_(band)","recorded":1375081352,"links":["/w/index.php